Gordo’s Cantina is INCREDIBLE! They are open and have a good outdoor dining set up. Can’t wait to go back! I tried the open faced poblano and corn burnt cheese quesadilla and the shrimp tacos - both hit it out of the park. For dessert, their key lime pie is the best I’ve ever tasted!!! It’s creamy with layers of cookies and to die for! And churros with cajeta caramel and chocolate sauce were SO delicious!

Mariah (hope I spelled her name right) was an AMAZING server. She suggested the flautas and the breaded white fish tacos. The fish was crunchy and soft and flaky on the inside, the flautas were so crunchy. I had the rumchata and it was strong and with a great balance of flavor.  I’d also recommend the shrimp ceviche, the presentation is beautiful and it tastes even better. 10/10 for the people in the kitchen because they are so consistent every single time, the food is always great.

Born and raised in the neighborhood. Seen a lot of businesses come and go. What makes this place stand out is the homemade tortillas. At first I was a little skeptical when I saw the tacos were $4 each. Pretty high for my standards to be honest, but then the order came in and I was super excited. What stood out was the warm greeting by the staff. The efficient kitchen workers, and the best part was the food. We try a sampler for tacos. Carne Asada, Chorizo, Pollo and Carnitas. The chicken and carnitas were my favorite due to how juicy they were. The flavor profile was great, not too much salt, the sauces were fresh and the tortilla is what always makes it breaks the deal for me! Super glad to have tried them and they have gained a new customer!

We have been big fans of the place when it was still located in LIC and we were very sad to see it leave the area. So this weekend we decided to take a 40 min trip down the memory lane to see how the new location is doing.  The menu was instantly recognizable as well as the no frills but homely interior. On the negative side, even in the new location the restaurant is still manages to be annoyingly drafty with a gust of icy wind whenever somebody enters or exits the place.  Also, sadly the taste did not live up to our memory of the place. The meats in tacos were just a little bit too dry and the sauces were not as rich in flavor and depth as we remembered.  It was still great food and good value for money just not as amazing as we had remembered it. If you are in the area definitely give it a try, and we would come back if it was anywhere closer to Queens but as it stands we don't think it's worth  the long trip to Bushwick.

Gordo's is a wonderful space for some great Mexican food from the Central Region of Mexico. The food is similar to what many might see from a taqueria with a more fresh and bright taste I found.  The star for me are the amazing breakfast burritas (slightly smaller than a normal burrito but packs flavor, consider ordering two) which you can get with normal egg bacon fare but I would highly recommend the chroizo and potato that blends perfectly with the bean spread.  For lunch the mole Enchiladas are filled with perfectly cooked fresh cheeses and doused in a flavorful, spiced, and familiar cocoa taste you expect with a great mole.  On top of all of this the prices are very reasonable portions are more than generous (one could argue the tacos are TOO stuffed with meat), and the staff is very polite.  For a small bite or a full meal this is a great spot to meet friends and have a fantastic meal in the neighborhood.

This new place recently opened in the neighborhood and my wife and l have been wanting to go till we finally did and I have to be honest the food is delicious service is great the place a a bit small but you feel at home comfortable and relaxed prices are reasonable and did I mention the great food

This small, colorful and clean location (situated on the corner of Stockholm Street and St. Nicholas Avenue) is a cantina in name only since it doesn't have a liquor license yet. The attentive and knowledgeable staff made me and my gf comfortable as we made our order. The guacamole was good and the fresh jalapenos gave it a spicy kick. The steak tacos, 3 to an order, were also good; as were the cecina enchilada tacos. The only nit to pick was that the cecina enchilada in this restaurant is not the salty, cured cecina normally served at other Mexican restaurants. The server explained that their cecina enchilada is pork similar to tacos al pastor. The regular cured cecina is not always available on their menu. Also, don't forget to visit their red light district/bathroom 😅 while you're in there. Overall, you could do worse than Gordo's. It's a good choice if you're nearby and need a quick and spicy taco hit.

I came here for dinner with a friend. Guac, tacos, quesadilla, and churros were all phenomenal! True authentic Mexican cuisine. The decor is super cute as well. The atmosphere is so comfortable and welcoming it feels like you’re going to your mom’s house! Staff is excellent as well. I will definitely be coming back.

The staff also accidentally forgot to put in our order, which we didn't really mind, but they were so nice about it, they sent some complimentary churros over. Yet another Long Island City spot that has inflated ratings due to the overwhelming demand for quality restaurants and lunch spots. The tacos here are not better than average, and certainly not as good as El Toro Rojo when the truck is parked by Court Square. The pollo taco is dry and not flavorful, the cochinita taco is also a little dry (they try to dress it up with pickled onions but still), the asada was one of the least remarkable asada tacos I have had in recent memory...the only truly great taco I had was the carnitas, which was flavorful and juicy as all get-out. They also tried to overcharge us for our beers, which were listed as $5 on the menu but $7 in their system. They should fix that.  Meh. This place benefits from a lack of any decent competition in the area. It could be so much better, but people in this neighborhood don't care because they're desperate for their "authentic" (overpriced yuppie-friendly) Mexican food. If this was competing with the taco spots in the Lower East Side or on the 7 train a few more stops out, it would have closed months ago.

Amazing place! Good things come in small packages. This place is a gem. I sat alone at the counter on a day off and was super impressed by the day manager. He was very polite, very professional and took pride in his job. Can't say enough about how great he was. Took the time to explain everything on the menu. I am a taco guy so I had chorizo tacos and chips and guac. Everything is made fresh to order in an open kitchen. The tacos were amazing, little salty, but amazing. I mean the best chorizo tacos I have ever had. For me, the chips are important. My family loves to start with chips and guac but some places the guac is not great and others, the chips not great. This place nailed it. Unfortunately, you get a small portion of guac for a large pile of chips but hey, lets face it, avocados are super expensive right now. I was so excited about the tacos that I went back the same day for dinner! I get really annoyed by taco places that won't let you mix the tacos. This place has a 4 taco sampler. Steak, chicken, chorizo and pork. The chorizo, as I said, was amazing, pork amazing, the steak was a little gristly, the chicken I could do without. I will give the steak another try as I see in the reviews that people like the steak. Long story short. I went twice in one day and I will be back 1,000 times. The word on the streets is that their sandwiches (tortas) are also excellent. One thing to consider is that they are smack dab next door to Scandals, a fairly large strip club. It is not unsafe. It is a very busy area next to the entrance to the Queensboro Bridge. Please don't let that dissuade you though but keep in mind that the music can be heard through the walls.

Very good hand made tortillas and tasteful shrimp tacos,  although no good selection of soft drinks and no beer or tequila at all.
The food was awesome. I would eat here every day if I could.
Great new addition to the neighborhood... I want a Pacifico with my tacos though ... hopefully they get a liquor license.
Had it for the first time at Electric Zoo and loved it! So I followed on Instagram and I have been to this spot, going again tonight! Fire up my Chapos! 😂
Thumbs up for the pulpo tacos!

Mexican cuisine is my favorite and I like the way they make their menu stand out with it's differences. Find out what the special is as it's always a great surprise, and why not end your meal with a delicious churro with caramel or chocolate?! The owners are always a delight and fun to talk with, they haven't steered me wrong once! Gordo's Cantina has become a lovely new staple in the neighborhood.

Great experience at this small restaurant!  Food was good, prices were right, and service was courteous and prompt.  The decor was simple but very nice.  We had the Mole Enchilada and some tacos, which were both great - the rice and beans were some of the best I've had.
Very good tacos and guacamole. It is a bit on the pricey side especially since the tacos do not come with any sides. We preferred the chicken and steak over the pork tacos.

A hair pricey, but 100% worth the cost. Some of the best homestyle Mexican I've had in the city - well worth the visit. The open face quesadillas are to DIE for.

This is not your average Mexican food. Please do not come expecting giant crappy cheese quesadillas. This is some of the most quality food I've ever had with a low-key, super chill vibe. Have the chorizo and try all salsas. The quesadillas are open-faced with crispy grilled cheese. Perfection. Not cheap. Worth it.

Tacos are literally on point. It's a little expensive but they have a woman making the tortillas from scratch! The food is very flavorful and the vibe is cool, just waiting for a liquor license, that is the only thing that will make things better! I'll definitely be back, try the churros and the chorizo burrito, it's awesome!!!
Smallest portions ever.

Amazing street style Mexican food!!! Small intimate atmosphere, great vibe!!! Service and food were excellent!!! The guacamole was probably the best I ever had (even better than my own). Can't wait to go back!!

Really incredible food! Everything is authentic and the prices are good. The chorizo burrito was honestly one of the best burritos I have had period! Tacos were on point CORN tortillas were made fresh to order!
